<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="184" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1307,1765]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,612,1307,1333]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Description and differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[620,743,1308,1334]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[620,688,1308,1333]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Xistra</emphasis>
spp.
</taxonomicName>
have the following characteristics: Size small, slender; body surface smooth. Head and eyes distinctly exserted above pronotal surface; vertex narrow, its width equal to or narrower than width of compound eye; vertex concave, its lateral margin exerted above the upper margin of eyes, seen from front, appearing as a “V”-shaped concavity or a “U”-shaped concavity between the eyes. Antennae filiform, antennal grooves inserted between or below inferior margins of compound eyes. Pronotum with anterior margin straight; humeral angles obtuse; hind process of pronotum long, cone-shaped. Lateral lobes of pronotum turned outwards, posterior margins with ventral sinus and tegminal (upper) sinus, apex of hind angle truncate. Visible part of tegmina oval; hindwings developed. Upper and lower margins of fore femora and middle femora entire, margins finely serrated; first segment of posterior tarsi equal to or slightly longer than third one.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1307,1765]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[199,267,1632,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[199,267,1632,1657]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Xistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Bolivar" authorityName="Bolivar" box="[498,686,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistrella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[498,593,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Xistrella</emphasis>
Bolívar
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bolivar" authorityName="Bolivar" box="[697,919,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Mazarredia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[697,828,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Mazarredia</emphasis>
Bolívar
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Bolivar" authorityName="Bolivar" box="[973,1208,1631,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Systolederus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[973,1115,1631,1657]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Systolederus</emphasis>
Bolívar
</taxonomicName>
, but differs from the three latter genera by the vertex, seen from front, appearing as an acute triangular excision between the eyes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1307,1765]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,569,1703,1729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Composition and distribution:</emphasis>
Altogether, 24 species are now assigned to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bolivar" authorityYear="1887" box="[1208,1276,1704,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Tetrigidae" genus="Xistra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="184" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1208,1276,1704,1729]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Xistra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and found in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,221,1739,1765]" name="China" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[232,361,1739,1765]" name="Philippines" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[372,487,1739,1765]" name="Cambodia" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Cambodia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[542,609,1739,1765]" name="Nepal" pageId="1" pageNumber="184">Nepal</collectingCountry>
(table1).
</paragraph>
